    <section class='overview module'>
      <h3>Overview</h3>
        <figure>
          <img alt="World Cup 2018 Russia Logo" src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/6/67/2018_FIFA_World_Cup.svg/1200px-2018_FIFA_World_Cup.svg.png">
        </figure>
        <p>Every four years, the world gathers to watch the greatest football players and teams compete against each other for the coveted World Cup. With matches being played inside beautiful stadiums packed with passionate fans, the world's biggest sporting tournament rarely dissapoints.</p>
        <p>Between the the 14th of June and the 15th of July, 32 teams will compete in <span class="bold">Russia</span>, playing in cities like Moscow, Saint Petersburg, Kazan, and Sochi.</p>
        <p>The teams come from far and wide representing each major region of the world ranging from North America to Asia. Featuring heavyweights like Germany, Brazil, France, and Spain as well as smaller, yet immensley talented countries like Panama, Iceland, and Morroco, the tournament is sure to provide only the highest quality of games.</p>
        <p>Each team is sorted into a group of four where each team plays one another once. At the end of the three matches, the top two teams in each group advance to the knockout stages.</p>
        <p>Each knockout fixture is hotly contested and brings the tournament closer and closer to the final in the <span class='bold'>Luzhuniki Stadium</span> in Moscow. Here, the world will find out which country is the greatest in the world.</p>
        <p>Get to know the teams, stadiums, and other information about the tournament before it begins. Below, you will find links to lead you to the information you want to know.</p>
    </section>

